          "defs": [
            "Destitute of consolation; deeply dejected and dispirited; hopelessly sad; comfortless; filled with grief; as, a bereaved and disconsolate parent."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "One morn a Peri at the gate Of Eden stood disconsolate.",
            "The ladies and the knights, no shelter nigh, Were dropping wet, disconsolate and wan."
